goals.question: What is the correlation between fertility and life expectancy?
goals.visualization: scatter plot of fertility vs life expectancy
goals.rationale: This visualization will help us understand if there is a relationship between fertility and life expectancy. If there is a negative correlation, it could indicate that countries with higher fertility rates have lower life expectancies.

goals.question: What is the distribution of fertility rates across countries?
goals.rationale: This visualization will help us understand the range of fertility rates across countries. It could also help identify any outliers or patterns in the data.

goals.question: What is the distribution of life expectancies across countries?
goals.rationale: This visualization will help us understand the range of life expectancies across countries. It could also help identify any outliers or patterns in the data.

goals.question: Which countries have the highest and lowest fertility rates?
goals.visualization: bar chart of fertility rates by country
goals.rationale: This visualization will help us identify the countries with the highest and lowest fertility rates. It could also help identify any regional patterns in the data.

goals.question: Which countries have the highest and lowest life expectancies?
goals.visualization: bar chart of life expectancies by country
goals.rationale: This visualization will help us identify the countries with the highest and lowest life expectancies. It could also help identify any regional patterns in the data.

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.scatter(data['fertility'], data['life_expect'])
    plt.xlabel('Fertility')
    plt.ylabel('Life Expectancy')
    plt.title('What is the correlation between fertility and life expectancy?')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

```
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.hist(data['fertility'], bins=20, color='green')
    plt.axvline(data['fertility'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Mean: {data['fertility'].mean():0.2f}")
    plt.axvline(data['fertility'].median(), color='blue', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Median: {data['fertility'].median():0.2f}")
    plt.xlabel('Fertility Rate')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.legend()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

```
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.dropna(subset=['life_expect'])
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    ax.hist(data['life_expect'], bins=20, color='blue', alpha=0.5)
    ax.axvline(data['life_expect'].median(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=2, label='Median Life Expectancy: {:.2f}'.format(data['life_expect'].median()))
    ax.set_xlabel('Life Expectancy')
    ax.set_ylabel('Frequency')
    ax.set_title('What is the distribution of life expectancies across countries?')
    ax.legend()
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

```
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.sort_values(by='fertility', ascending=False)
    top_5 = data.head(5)
    bottom_5 = data.tail(5)
    countries = top_5['country'].tolist() + bottom_5['country'].tolist()
    fertility_rates = top_5['fertility'].tolist() + bottom_5['fertility'].tolist()
    colors = ['red']*5 + ['blue']*5
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(12,6))
    ax.bar(countries, fertility_rates, color=colors)
    ax.axhline(y=data['fertility'].median(), color='gray', linestyle='--', label='Median Fertility Rate: {:.2f}'.format(data['fertility'].median()))
    ax.set_xlabel('Country')
    ax.set_ylabel('Fertility Rate')
    ax.set_title('Which countries have the highest and lowest fertility rates?')
    ax.legend()
    plt.xticks(rotation=45, ha='right')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.sort_values(by='life_expect')
    countries = data['country']
    life_expect = data['life_expect']
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 8))
    ax.barh(countries, life_expect, color='green')
    ax.axvline(x=life_expect.min(), color='red', linestyle='--', label='Min life expectancy: {:.2f}'.format(life_expect.min()))
    ax.axvline(x=life_expect.max(), color='blue', linestyle='--', label='Max life expectancy: {:.2f}'.format(life_expect.max()))
    ax.legend()
    ax.set_xlabel('Life Expectancy')
    ax.set_ylabel('Country')
    ax.set_title('Which countries have the highest and lowest life expectancies?')
    plt.tight_layout()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```
